mods.abstract:
Interview describes Breazeale's experiences as a student at Louisiana State
            University and member of the Kappa Kappa Gamma sorority. She describes LSU social life;
            women's clothing; layout and use of the Panhellenic Building; dormitory rules;
            ceremonies and traditions; the push for the construction of sorority houses; her
            thoughts on LSU today; and problems with the Legislature and university funding. Focus
            dates: 1940-1960s.
